{
  "id": 55597,
  "kuerzel": "M_TecBEC",
  "bezeichnung": "English Beyond Borders: Navigating Academic & Professional Success with IELTS",
  "kreditpunkte": 4,
  "lernziele": "<p>Designed for language levels B2 to C1, preparing students for effective communication in diverse academic and professional settings.<br />Students learn to critically reflect the role of technology in modern society today as well as its representation in the media. Ethical considerations related to technology in academic and professional contexts will also be explored. By the end of the module, students will be capable of passing the IELTS examination. The IELTS is a globally recognized English language proficiency test, designed for individuals who need to demonstrate their ability to communicate in English, especially for academic or work purposes. Precision and appropriateness of language is taught in a number of discourse situations, such as</p>\n<p>- panel discussions (learn how to participate in and moderate panel discussions)<br />- project work (understand and apply project management principles in a team setting).<br />- debating and discussing (foster critical thinking skills through engaging in discussions and debates).<br />- presentation skills (receive constructive feedback and improve presentation techniques)</p>",
  "semesterBewertung": "Note von 1 - 6",
  "sprache": "de-CH",
  "zustand": "aktiviert",
